# Certified Appsec Practitioner (CAP)

<figure><img src="https://3577347090-files.gitbook.io/~/files/v0/b/gitbook-x-prod.appspot.com/o/spaces%2FWrIcinZ87qSasUAtuqcU%2Fuploads%2FcPyPht0VEMRg4QfWZxjL%2Fimage.png?alt=media&#x26;token=f3ee6355-6c98-4bf1-8046-085fedde7668" alt=""><figcaption></figcaption></figure>

Since the **SecOps Group** came up with a voucher that offered free certification to **Certified Appsec Practitioner** I will be creating notes here. I will be working on the Certified Appsec Practitioner.

The Course Contents for Certified Appsec Practitioner are as follows:

1. [Input Validation Mechanisms](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/input-validation-mechanisms)

* [*Blacklisting*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/whitelisting-and-blacklisting)
* [*Whitelisting*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/whitelisting-and-blacklisting)

2\. [Cross-Site Scripting](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/cross-site-scripting)

3\. [SQL Injection](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/sql-injection)

4\. [XML External Entity attack](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/xml-external-entity-attack)

5\. [Cross-Site Request Forgery](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/cross-site-request-forgery)

6\. [Encoding, Encryption, and Hashing](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/encoding-encryption-and-hashing)

7\. [Authentication related Vulnerabilities](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/authentication-related-vulnerabilities)

* [*Brute force Attacks*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/brute-force-attacks)
* [*Password Storage and Password Policy*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/password-storage-and-password-policy)

8\. [Understanding of OWASP Top 10 Vulnerabilities](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/understanding-of-owasp-top-10-vulnerabilities)

9\. [Security Best Practices and Hardening Mechanisms.](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/same-origin-policy)

* [*Same Origin Policy*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/same-origin-policy)
* [*Security Headers.*](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/security-headers.)

10. [TLS security](https://rkive.gitbook.io/certified-appsec-practitioner-cap/tls-security)

